{
 "name": "RPlog_Visiting_Roark",
 "title": "Visiting Roark: An Unlikely Friendship",
 "summary": "Aboard the New Republic vessel Hyperon, the flight tech Jessalyn visits the detained Corellian businessman Xegid Roark, finding him hungover and despondent on the floor of his quarters. She brings him flowers grown from Yavin IV cuttings and, over a warm conversation about luxury liners, loneliness, and his estranged daughter Melisan--taken from him by a Corellian court ruling him an unfit father--the two strike up a genuine friendship. The arrival of Councilor Antra Silverthorn and Chewbacca turns the visit tense and political; while Roark fences with Antra over the New Republic's inadequate proposals, Jessalyn quietly feeds Chewbacca the intelligence she has gleaned, including Roark's daughter and possible Corellian leverage that might secure Han Solo's return. Later, alone again, Roark comforts a tearful Jessalyn over her own past regrets, and the two share a tender moment of mutual encouragement to make fresh starts before she departs, leaving the rose plant--and a hopeful Roark--behind.",
 "rows": [
